msItem.title: Guta lag
msItem.incipit: Dette er først for alt ophaab oc begindelsse vdi vor lou:
msItem.note: Fol. 68r contains a first attempt at the text that has been re-written on 14r.

foliation.p: The main scribe has paginated 2-113 on every recto and verso from 3v-59r. A later hand has foliated 1+1bis-69 on every recto.

collation.signatures: The letter B can be found on 13r; otherwise there are no quire signatures.
collation.catchwords: There are catchwords on nearly every page.

condition.p: The manuscript is in generally good condition.

list.item: The text is written in one column with 17 to 21 lines per page.

handDesc.handNote: A single hand has written the main text using a cursive script.
Claus Christophersen Lyschander has written items 1 and 4 and has made marginal notes in the main text.

decoDesc.p: New chapters begin with enlarged initials.

binding.p:
The binding is made of repurposed parchment originally containing a Latin missal. The title IVS
GOTLAN
DICVM is written on the front cover.

A paper cover once served as the outermost cover and contains the title DEN
GAMLE
GVLLANDS
LOW. During restoration in 2013, this paper cover was removed and placed in a plastic sleeve.

origin.p: Kålund, Katalog I375 dates it to ca. 1600.

provenance.p: The manuscript was owned by Claus Christophersen Lyschander, who wrote items 1 and 4. Árni Magnússon purchased the manuscript from Frederik Rostgaard's collection in 1726 for 1 mark and 8 shillings.

list.item: Black and white photographs from 1981; supplementary photographs from 1982.
Digital portraits before restauration taken in 2012; after restauration in 2014.
Digital photographs of the entire manuscript taken in 2017.
